Harmon Seaver <hseaver@harmon.arrowhead.lib.mn.us> wrote:
> A really
> nice thing would be a mail client that did automagic crypt, plus a
> mixmaster component to hide the true name of the sender or receiver
> running on linux.

Try mutt.  It allows you to default to signing or encrypting all
outgoing mail.  It supports mixmaster.  It slices, it dices, etc.

http://www.mutt.org

The only thing it doesn't do is handle HTMLized mail, but you can have
it call an external program (lynx, netscape, whatever) to do this for
you.

